The paper deals with the analysis of pseudocodewords in Tanner graphs, which are commonly used in coding theory and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the properties of iterative decoding, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The analysis of graph properties and design of Tanner graphs could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
